Name: cervical benign neoplasm
Definition: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the cervix.

Name: cervical polyp
Definition: A cervix disease characterized by a benign polyp on the surface of the cervical canal.

Name: hypertrophic elongation of cervix
Definition: A disease characterized by a group of signs and symptoms that occur together and characterize a particular abnormality.
Synonym: Thoracic or lumbar spondylosis with myelopathy

Name: cervicitis
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by inflammation of the cervix.

Name: cervix erosion
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by the presence of enodcervical columnar epithelium on the ectocervix.

Name: cervix endometriosis
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by the growth endometrial tissue that is located on the cervix.

Name: uterine cervix leukoplakia
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by the presence of a hyperkeratotic lesion.

Name: obsolete nodular lymphoma involving lymph nodes of multiple sites
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by the presence of a hyperkeratotic lesion.
Synonym: nodular lymphoma of lymph nodes of multiple sites (disorder)

Name: cervical incompetence
Definition: A cervix disease that is characterized by the beginning of dilation and effacement of a pregnant woman's cervix before her pregnancy has reached term.
